snippet.textDisplay:
To all these babyragers in the comments:
1. Yes there are a lot of dps heroes, that is because they were categorized as offense and defense initially so the first dps pool was twice the size of tanks and supports.

2. The devs cycle the releases, it's dps -> support -> tank (Brig -> Hammond -> Ashe -> bap -> sigma -> echo)

3. Echo is the last hero to be released in OW1 so either learn more tanks/supports to achieve your desired variety or take a break until OW2.

4. It takes MANY months to take a hero from design to playability so even if they were going to deviate from the cycle to appease the support/tank mains that feel as though they are forced to play one hero (rein for example) it wouldn't have been noticed until this fall release or the release after that (keep in mind there's no more OW1 heroes)

5. " there is a big list of support and tanks in development for Overwatch 2." -Papa Jeff

How to save overwatch
1.Ven cards are created by voting for each team (two per team).
2. Rank game for up to 2 players only
3. When 8 people report (automatic stop for 1 day, 1 week, 1 month / permanent stop after review)-including non-manners and hacking
4. One season per year. Platinum and above receive one golden weapon voucher once the season ends.
5. Sell skins such as LOL
6. If you decide to play the main role before the match and play, you can select all the champions and the role is decided. 2 Dealer 2 Healer 2 Tanker
7. No fun hero reorganization (Healer can carry)

snippet.textDisplay:
Anyone notice that Jeff gave us I big piece of lore info?
When he was talking about how liao made friends with the overwatch members he specifically mentioned McCree and that he was basically her body guard
He also states that she died when "an overwatch facility was attacked" this is significant because in retrebution's opening the 1st sentence is - "An overwatch facility was attacked" and it shows McCree standing in front a building that just got bombed. Also in echos origin story you can see that Dr. Liao was caught up in an explosion

So if you put 2 and 2 together everything matches up and we get a solid piece of info of when this happens and ties together the lore

Also I really couldn't help but to feel like Jeff worded it this way and it felt like he put a lot of emphasise on this.
